      "title": "STAVE TWO. — THE FIRST OF THE THREE SPIRITS.",
      "metadata": {
        "scene_summary": {
          "description": "Scrooge awakens in his dark bedroom, confused by the chiming clocks. After wrestling with time and memory, he encounters the Ghost of Christmas Past—a luminous, shape-shifting spirit. They journey through Scrooge's memories: his lonely schooldays, his sister Fan's joyful rescue, Fezziwig's generous Christmas party, and his lost love Belle. The scenes grow increasingly painful until Scrooge desperately fights to extinguish the Ghost's light.",
          "important_details": [
            "Setting shifts from Scrooge's dark bedroom to various locations from his past",
            "Time is disoriented—clocks strike twelve when it should be early morning",
            "Ghost emanates bright light from its head, wears white tunic with summer flowers",
            "Locations include: countryside road, old school, Fezziwig's warehouse, Belle's parlour",
            "Mood progresses from confusion to nostalgia to deep regret and anguish"
